Language: Dagaare
Language code: gur
Lines: orth orth-seg gloss translat
Author: Drew Owens, Graham Still
Date: January 17, 2018
Source a: Bodomo, A. B. (1997). The structure of Dagaare. Cambridge: Cambridge Univ. Press.

#=======================#
#      Word order       #
#=======================#

# 1
# Adapted from a:41
# Intransitive example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
badɛr kpie la
badɛr  kpi-e         la
spider die-PERF.INTR FACT
'spider dies'

# 2
# Adapted from a:114
# Transitive example
# SVO
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
a bader boɔro la koɔraa
a   badɛr  boɔ-ro   la   koɔraa
DEF spidɛr love-IPFV FACT farmer
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 3
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical SOV example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
a badɛr koɔraa boɔro la
a   badɛr  koɔraa boɔ-ro    la   
DEF spidɛr farmer love-IPFV FACT 
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 4
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical VSO example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
boɔro la a bader koɔraa 
boɔ-ro    la   DEF badɛr  koɔraa 
love-IPFV FACT the spidɛr farmer 
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 5
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical VOS example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
boɔro la koɔraa a bader
boɔ-ro    la   koɔraa a   badɛr
love-IPFV FACT farmer DEF spidɛr 
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 6
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical OSV example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
koɔraa a bader boɔro la
koɔraa a   badɛr  boɔ-ro    la
farmer DEF spidɛr love-IPFV FACT  
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 7
# Adapted from a:114
# Ungrammatical OVS example
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: word order
koɔraa boɔro la a bader
koɔraa boɔ-ro    la   a   badɛr  
farmer love-IPFV FACT DEF spidɛr  
'the spider loves a farmer'

# 8
# Adapted from a:42
# Ditransitive
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: word order
naa ko koɔraa la gane
naa   ko        koɔraa la   gane
chief give.PERF farmer FACT book
'I give a farmer a book'

#=======================#
#       Pronouns        #
#=======================#

# 1
# Weak form
Source: a:91
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: pronouns
n mi
n         mi  
1s.NOM.WK know
'I know'

# 2
# Strong form
# Adapted from a:91
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: pronouns
maa mi
maa        mi
1s.NOM.STR know
'I, for one, know'

# 3
# Weak form
# Adapted from a:114
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: pronouns
fo boɔro la koɔraa
fo        boɔ-ro    la   koɔraa
2s.NOM.WK love-IPFV FACT farmer
'you love a farmer'

# 4
# Strong form
# Adapted from a:114
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgement: g
Phenomena: pronouns
foo boɔro la koɔraa
foo        boɔ-ro    la   koɔraa
2s.NOM.STR love-IPFV FACT farmer
'you, in particular, love a farmer'

# 5
# Weak form
# Adapted from a:41
# The zero-affixed ngmɛ in all likelihood indicates PERF.TR
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: pronouns
